  "prompt": "What are some lesser-known sights to see when visiting Purnia, Bihar, India?",
  "response": "While Purnia is not as well-known as some other tourist destinations in India, there are a few interesting sights to explore:\n\n1. Kali Mandir\n- An important local temple dedicated to Goddess Kali\n- Popular among religious visitors\n\n2. Phulbaria Market\n- A bustling local market showcasing traditional Bihar culture\n- Good for experiencing local life and shopping\n\n3. Triveni Sangam\n- Confluence point of three rivers\n- Scenic spot with religious significance\n\n4. Purnia District Museum\n- Small museum showcasing local history and cultural artifacts\n- Offers insights into the region's heritage\n\n5. Nearkal Dam\n- A scenic water reservoir\n- Good for picnics and enjoying natural landscapes\n\n6. Local Handicraft Centers\n- Opportunities to see traditional Bihar handicrafts\n- Chance to purchase local handmade items\n\n7. Shahid Smarak\n- Memorial commemorating local freedom fighters\n- Historical significance\n\nPlease note that Purnia is a relatively small city, and tourism infrastructure might be limited. These suggestions are based on local attractions, and it's recommended to verify current accessibility and conditions before visiting.",
